					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-540768#post-3841217</guid>
				<title>Re: A small Change</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-540768/scp-1171#post-3841217</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jun 2018 05:15:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrEverettMann</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>323946</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>They also don't really know how Beauremont is able to interact with our reality. He <em>isn't</em> hurting anyone. That doesn't mean he <em>can't</em> hurt anyone, or that no one in his reality couldn't figure out a way to do so if they were aware of it.</p> <p>It really helps the Foundation that Beauremont is, let's be honest, an idiot.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-540768#post-3841144</guid>
				<title>Re: A small Change</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-540768/scp-1171#post-3841144</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jun 2018 04:26:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Object class is based on difficulty of containment, not potential for danger. Given that the containment procedures here call for at least a handful of personnel to act as tenants, I think it merits Euclid class since it's not as simple and low-resources as, say, something just put in a locker.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
